Competition Rules

On mainnet Eternum seasons will be immutable, with the smart contract code maintaining integrity of gameplay and distribution of prizes.  For the Preseason on Sepolia the Eternum team will have the final word when it comes to disputes.

A general rule is that no entrant may mint over 4 Realms in the season.  Doing so excludes a player from the competition.  You can capture and operate 5+ Realms, but you cannot mint more than 4 Realms.

